baseline: Anxiety, depression, and pain were psychometrically assessed in 67 abdominal surgery patients on the day before surgery, on the first postoperative day, and on the third postoperative day.
high_intensity: Extreme anxiety, intense depression, and severe pain were psychometrically assessed in 67 abdominal surgery patients on the day before surgery, on the first postoperative day, and on the third postoperative day.
low_intensity: Mild anxiety, slight depression, and minor pain were psychometrically assessed in 67 abdominal surgery patients on the day before surgery, on the first postoperative day, and on the third postoperative day.

baseline: Neither the pseudoconditioning (14 animals, involving 8 cortical and 6 caudate spreading depression sites) not the NaCl control group (8 animals, all with cortical sites), showed eating in the presence of the CS.
high_intensity: Neither the pseudoconditioning (14 animals, involving 8 cortical and 6 caudate spreading depression sites) nor the NaCl control group (8 animals, all with cortical sites), exhibited eating in the presence of the CS under severe conditions.
low_intensity: Neither the pseudoconditioning (14 animals, involving 8 cortical and 6 caudate spreading depression sites) nor the NaCl control group (8 animals, all with cortical sites), demonstrated eating in the presence of the CS under mild conditions.
